---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LabelRow from '../components/LabelRow.astro';
import CtaStrip from '../components/CtaStrip.astro';

const facts = [
  ['Based', 'Minneapolis, <em>MN</em>'],
  ['Available', 'Remote, US-wide'],
  ['Capacity', '1–2 new this quarter'],
  ['Reply time', '≤ 2 business days'],
  ['Past clients', 'Small biz, <em>universities, brokers</em>'],
  ['Stack', 'Whatever fits the job'],
  ['Meeting style', 'In person where possible'],
  ['Billing', 'Hourly, <em>or fixed scope</em>']
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — NSG Solutions"
  description="Noah Greensweig runs NSG Solutions, a one-person custom software practice in Minneapolis. End-to-end engagements, no handoffs, no account managers."
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="about-hero">
        <div>
          <LabelRow num="ABOUT / 01" meta="The person behind it" />
          <h1>Hi — I'm Noah.<br /><em>I run a small software practice<br />out of Minneapolis.</em></h1>
        </div>
        <div class="about-photo-frame">
          <img src="/assets/noah.jpg" alt="Noah Greensweig" />
          <div class="about-photo-tag"><span class="dash"></span>Noah Greensweig · Minneapolis, MN</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">02 / WHAT THIS IS</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            NSG is a small software practice. The whole thing is one person: I take on
            a handful of client engagements at a time, I do the work end-to-end, and the
            person you talk to is the same person writing the code.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've spent years writing software in full-time roles — most recently building an
            automation layer over a reinsurance broker's catastrophe-modeling pipeline,
            and leading AI adoption inside the same business. NSG is where I bring that
            experience to small businesses that want a real tool, not a slide deck about one.
          </p>
          <p>
            The pitch is plain. <em>Do business with integrity. Stick with the work
            until you look at it and feel: this is better than what we had in mind.</em>
            That's it. There's no second pitch.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">03 / HOW THIS WORKS</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            We meet — in person if you're in or near Minneapolis, video otherwise.
            You walk me through what's getting in the way of the work. I ask a lot of
            questions, take notes, and come back with a plain-language proposal:
            what the fix looks like, what it costs (hourly rate, or a fixed bid for well-defined work),
            and when you'll have it.
          </p>
          <p>
            Then we build, together. You see the work as it goes — not in a reveal at the end.
            Things change as we learn; that's fine. The point isn't to defend the original
            plan, it's to land the right thing.
          </p>
          <p>
            When it's done, it's yours. I write things so a person who isn't me can keep
            them running. If something we previously agreed was finished later turns out to
            be broken, fixing it is free.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">04 / ON AI</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            There's no single right AI tool, and the landscape changes every few months.
            Part of the job is keeping track of that so you don't have to, and picking
            the thing that fits your situation — not the thing that's trending this week.
          </p>
          <p>
            Used carefully, AI makes a lot of this work faster than it used to be, which
            mostly means projects are cheaper and ship sooner. Quality doesn't suffer for
            it. Used carelessly, it makes a confident mess. Most of the craft now is knowing
            the difference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-facts">
        <LabelRow num="05 / FACTS" meta="The short version" />
        <div class="facts-grid">
          {facts.map(([key, value]) => (
            <div class="fact">
              <div class="key">{key}</div>
              <div class="val" set:html={value}></div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <CtaStrip
      title="Want to talk?"
      continuation="Tell me what's going on."
      note="Two business-day reply · No commitment until you're ready"
      primaryText="Get in touch"
      ghostText="Email directly"
    />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
